## Overview

Redesign AI Terminal from full-width bottom overlay to right-hand sidebar with theme-adaptive styling.

**Current Problems:**
1. AI Terminal takes up 50% of screen height (too large)
2. Full-width overlay blocks all user interaction when open
3. Generic chat UI doesn't match terminal aesthetic user requested

**User Requirements:**
1. Right-hand sidebar (mirrors left navigation sidebar)
2. Collapsible (keep existing toggle behavior)
3. Terminal-style UI with theme support:
   - **Dark mode:** Black background, white user text, green AI text
   - **Light mode:** White background, black user text, orange AI text
4. Users can work while AI is open (non-blocking)

---

## Problem Statement

### Current Architecture (Bottom Overlay)
```tsx
<div className="fixed bottom-0 right-0 left-0 h-96 md:h-[500px]">
  {/* Full-width overlay taking 50% height */}
</div>
```

**Issues:**
- Full-width blocks content behind it
- Fixed height (h-96 md:h-[500px]) is 384px-500px (~50% on 1080p)
- Generic chat UI (white/dark bg, gradient header)
- User can't interact with anything else when open

### Desired Architecture (Right Sidebar)
```tsx
<div className={`
  fixed top-0 right-0 h-screen
  ${isOpen ? 'translate-x-0' : 'translate-x-full'}
  w-[400px] lg:w-[500px]
  // Terminal-style colors (theme-adaptive)
  bg-white dark:bg-black
  border-l border-border-light dark:border-border-dark
  z-40
`}>
  {/* Terminal UI */}
</div>
```

**Benefits:**
- Right sidebar doesn't block main content
- User can interact with dashboard/widgets while AI is open
- Terminal aesthetic (monospace font, color-coded messages)
- Theme-adaptive (light/dark mode support)
- Matches left sidebar size and behavior

